Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.01,Dialogue,Credits,0,0,0,,Subtitle-source: Detective Conan - 234 [AZFS][0BFB42BC].avi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.31,0:00:06.27,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.31,0:00:06.27,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Song by Matsuhashi Miki
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.68,0:00:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hint to reasoning is to dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.60,0:00:05.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a mystery behind every case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.27,0:00:09.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Doyle the dog went missing, the\Nbreeders became surprisingly honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.90,0:00:11.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeking the one and only truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.74,0:00:13.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.53,0:00:15.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is... Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.95,0:00:17.74,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,Something's just not right
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.95,0:00:17.74,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,Something's just not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.37,0:00:21.91,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,nani o motometeru no
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.37,0:00:21.91,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,What is it we're seeking?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.41,0:00:26.63,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,uso ni narete yuku kyou mo fake your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.41,0:00:26.63,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,We're used to lying nowadays, as you fake your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.38,0:00:32.67,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,The start of century
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.38,0:00:32.67,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,The start of century.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.01,0:00:36.14,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,tashika na mono nakute
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.01,0:00:36.14,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,Nothing can be considered certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.14,0:00:41.22,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,hitori ja nakenai yowasa hate myself
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.14,0:00:41.22,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,I can't cry over my weaknesses, I can only hate myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.48,0:00:50.94,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,shinjiteru itami hikikae ni kono mune umetsukushite
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.48,0:00:50.94,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,Believing in this pain, my chest endures through the exhaustion.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.48,0:00:59.83,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,ima utsutte iru futari ga eranda michi kuru
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.48,0:00:59.83,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,The future in which the two of us can be together is coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.08,0:01:03.45,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,I think it's only my destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.08,0:01:03.45,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,I think it's only my destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.70,0:01:06.83,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,hateshinai yami no mukou ni
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.70,0:01:06.83,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,On the other side of this persistent darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.17,0:01:13.17,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,dare mo shiru koto no nai ashita ga aru
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.17,0:01:13.17,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,There's a tomorrow that has no time limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.46,0:01:18.18,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,oh yeah. You're going nowhere, It's only destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.46,0:01:18.18,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,Oh yeah. You're going nowhere, It's only destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.43,0:01:21.47,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,ari no mama ni susunde
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.43,0:01:21.47,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,Looking for that final resolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.68,0:01:28.77,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,ima kanjite iru you're in my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.68,0:01:28.77,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,I can feel you now, you're in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.86,0:01:32.82,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,you're in my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.86,0:01:32.82,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,You're in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.58,0:01:50.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We visited Professor Agasa's friend, Kanou Teruya-san, to\Nselect items he was giving to friends before moving away.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.09,0:01:53.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later on, we were joined by...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.42,0:01:55.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsunashima Yoshio-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.80,0:01:57.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsobayashi Aki-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.05,0:01:59.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Hasuki Shino-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.72,0:02:04.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Different desires were aroused as they\Ngathered here to obtain things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.89,0:02:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then a prized Papillon dog went missing from the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.06,0:02:16.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, we discovered Doyle's\Ncollar, that was cut by a knife,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.15,0:02:19.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,burning in the incinerator.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.16,0:02:23.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.08,0:02:24.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...Doyle's!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.99,0:02:27.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a lie... It's a lie...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.96,0:02:35.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? That's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.09,0:02:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were only two blue cushions\Nwhen we came here earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.72,0:02:42.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Including the one Arthur brought out,\Nthere are now three cushions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.93,0:02:46.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's one extra.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.64,0:02:49.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.98,0:02:57.69,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,The Evidence That Didn't Disappear
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.98,0:02:57.69,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,(Part 2)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.95,0:03:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the clock chimed at noon, Doyle ran to the Japanese\Nroom where he gets his snack, disappearing from our sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.08,0:03:16.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We then went with Kanou-san to the kitchen,\Nwhere he prepared a plate of cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.55,0:03:20.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, we noticed that Doyle was nowhere\Nto be found in the Japanese room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.42,0:03:23.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then everyone split up to search in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.84,0:03:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even with a diagram of the house, I don't\Nknow where each person searched.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.64,0:03:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, where could the culprit have hidden him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.90,0:03:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, how was he planning to get Doyle out of here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.11,0:03:42.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This has become a bad time to move hasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.66,0:03:44.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.03,0:03:45.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moving out...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.70,0:03:53.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said that we can have the things that you're not\Nbringing with you. Can we take them home today?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.54,0:03:56.42,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Teruya Kanou (26)\NProfessor Agasa's Friend's Son
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.54,0:03:56.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's fine with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.54,0:03:58.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are the rest of them taking their things home today as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.88,0:04:03.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Tsunashima-san will be taking his clock tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.59,0:04:03.72,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Yoshio Tsunashima (45)\NDog Breeder
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.05,0:04:08.68,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Shino Hasuki (27)\NDog Breeder
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.05,0:04:08.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hasuki-san won't be taking the stereo for\Nanother ten days, a day before I leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.68,0:04:12.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though I said she could have\Nit now since I hardly use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.56,0:04:17.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're both here today to see another\Nantique that I found in the Southeast.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.32,0:04:24.95,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Aki Tosabayashi (39)\NDog Breeder
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.69,0:04:20.78,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And even though Tsobayashi-san showed up unannounced,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.78,0:04:24.53,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,judging by her personality, she'll most\Nlikely take the vase home today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.28,0:04:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure that vase is in the living room! Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.00,0:04:32.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doyle is inside the vase?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.88,0:04:39.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not likely, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.17,0:04:45.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even the stereo that's being moved in\Nten days can't hide a small animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.93,0:04:52.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's impossible to hide a dog in the\Nclock from the Japanese room too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.10,0:04:57.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? That clock is five minutes behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.23,0:05:02.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's weird. It's never been wrong since we repaired it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.69,0:05:06.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute. When I saw the clock\Nearlier, I'm pretty sure it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.83,0:05:11.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this cotton-like thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.62,0:05:13.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like some sort of chemical fiber.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.54,0:05:16.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, let me see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.88,0:05:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.17,0:05:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That glittering cotton was on the\Ncushion Arthur found as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.30,0:05:29.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute! Where have I seen\Nthis kind of material before?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.68,0:05:33.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The incinerator!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.85,0:05:39.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.23,0:05:42.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could Doyle have been burnt in there after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.19,0:05:45.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I checked earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.90,0:05:49.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought this was just burnt rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.45,0:05:52.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt. This is glass wool,\Na sound absorbing material!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.70,0:05:55.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.29,0:05:57.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what the culprit used!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.04,0:05:59.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.63,0:06:03.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've figured out where Doyle is hidden,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.25,0:06:05.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the method used to hide him,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.09,0:06:06.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the intention behind it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.09,0:06:09.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and who the culprit is!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.35,0:06:15.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already this late?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.35,0:06:19.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be leaving then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.81,0:06:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me too. I have to prepare dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.94,0:06:24.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,P-Please hold on for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.23,0:06:29.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, just accept this as bad luck and give up on that dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.61,0:06:31.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.79,0:06:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.04,0:06:38.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The clock in the Japanese room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.37,0:06:42.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's only supposed to ring at noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.29,0:06:43.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.05,0:06:50.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.47,0:06:53.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We did it, Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.35,0:06:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll now go and make the preparations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.68,0:06:57.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.85,0:06:59.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What preparation?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.48,0:07:01.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're going to do an experiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.10,0:07:08.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to see if the criminal could really hide Doyle\Nwithout anyone noticing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.57,0:07:12.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How foolish, have you forgotten that Doyle is still missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.99,0:07:18.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The leading part of this experiment, of course, goes to Doyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.54,0:07:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doyle!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.58,0:07:24.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You found him!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.34,0:07:27.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.01,0:07:34.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come watch the experiment then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.14,0:07:41.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll begin in the corridor where Doyle was last seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.81,0:07:48.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez. Isn't it enough that the dog has been found?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.19,0:07:52.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to play along with some\Nchildren's detective game.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.57,0:07:54.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.99,0:07:58.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko, you can begin now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.20,0:07:59.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roger that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.04,0:08:04.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that clock again!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.88,0:08:11.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. When Doyle heard the clock chime,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.63,0:08:14.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he ran towards the Japanese room\Nfor his cheese snack as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.14,0:08:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We also headed there after stopping by the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.68,0:08:20.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what happened, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.02,0:08:21.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.77,0:08:24.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now then, where do you think Doyle is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.27,0:08:31.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What foolishness. He always gets his snacks in the\NJapanese room, so of course he's there now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.11,0:08:35.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? He's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.78,0:08:40.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, the chime didn't come from the Japanese room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.37,0:08:41.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.00,0:08:44.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What in the...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.04,0:08:46.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kanou-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.71,0:08:49.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chime came from the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.42,0:08:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The living room?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.17,0:08:57.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't mean that the sound came from the stereo?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.64,0:08:58.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.60,0:09:05.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We recorded the chime from the Japanese\Nroom earlier, and played it here,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.02,0:09:08.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,using this tape recorder I borrowed from Nii-san's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.11,0:09:13.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Doyle followed the clock's sound here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.24,0:09:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not possible with the chime alone,\Nthere must be a cushion as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.61,0:09:17.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cushion?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.91,0:09:23.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, didn't you tell us that Doyle would\Nsit on his cushion to wait for his snack?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.54,0:09:28.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Doyle's favorite blue cushion\Nis in the Japanese room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.17,0:09:31.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doyle likes the blue cushion not because of its color.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.55,0:09:37.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A dog's sense of hearing is four times that of a human's. Its\Nsense of smell is also much stronger than a human's, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.26,0:09:39.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They cannot distinguish colors at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.89,0:09:47.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Doyle always picked out the cushion\Nwith his scent during snack time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.23,0:09:49.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cushion just happened to be blue in color, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.27,0:09:54.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means Doyle wasn't waiting\Nin the Japanese room at noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.57,0:10:01.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rather, he remembers that if he sits on his usual cushion\Nnear where the chime is, he will get a snack.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.04,0:10:08.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Knowing that, the culprit used it to\Nhis advantage to get the dog here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.79,0:10:15.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are teeth marks left on Doyle's usual cushion,\Nso it's easy for the criminal to identify.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.67,0:10:24.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Tsunashima-san and I searched this living\Nroom and we didn't find anything at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.31,0:10:25.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Neither the dog nor the cushion, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.22,0:10:26.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.02,0:10:28.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're here, just well hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.52,0:10:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.36,0:10:34.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, behind the stereo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.07,0:10:36.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.70,0:10:41.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? The back of the speaker is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.79,0:10:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit removed the sound absorbing material\Nthat filled the speaker's interior in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.46,0:10:56.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doyle's favorite cushion was then placed in\Nthat space, along with a piece of cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.21,0:11:01.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, the right speaker had\Nbeen adjusted to be soundless.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.59,0:11:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, he played the recorded sound\Nof the chime from the left speaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.02,0:11:18.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Doyle was drawn here by the chime, the smell of his\Ncushion, and the cheese, and went into the speaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.03,0:11:22.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wouldn't he come out after eating the cheese?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.61,0:11:27.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He fell asleep after eating the sleeping\Npill that was placed in the cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.08,0:11:37.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But would it have gone so smoothly? If it was noon\Nat that time, the real clock would have chimed too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.75,0:11:39.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it couldn't chime,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.34,0:11:43.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because the clock was moved forward 12 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.01,0:11:53.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The wall clock is set to chime only at noon. So, if\Nit's moved forward 12 hours, then it won't chime.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.40,0:11:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who would do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.40,0:11:58.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.44,0:11:58.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.32,0:12:04.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't think of anyone else but Hasuki-san\Nwho wanted that stereo, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.82,0:12:06.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.99,0:12:11.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She must have planned to hide the dog\Nin the speaker, then steal it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.79,0:12:14.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't—! I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.79,0:12:17.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.04,0:12:20.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way that Hasuki-san would have gone that far to—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.01,0:12:24.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But weren't her shoes left right\Nnext to the incinerator earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.18,0:12:25.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.14,0:12:25.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.97,0:12:26.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.35,0:12:29.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is not Hasuki-san.
Comment: 0,0:12:31.81,0:12:35.27,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Based off Manga\NVolume 29, Files 6-8
Comment: 0,0:12:31.81,0:12:35.27,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Original Air Date\NMay 21st, 2001
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.73,0:12:38.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is not Hasuki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.27,0:12:40.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.11,0:12:45.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the stereo won't be taken\Nuntil ten days from now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.32,0:12:49.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way a dog can stay alive\Nlocked in there that long, can it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.70,0:12:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if it wasn't Hasuki-san, then why\Nwas it hidden in the speaker?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.33,0:13:01.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit wasn't planning to steal Doyle, but rather\Nwanted to keep him hidden temporarily, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.55,0:13:03.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hidden temporarily?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.01,0:13:09.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even if that's a blind spot, the dog would be found\Nimmediately if the back of the speaker fell open.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.39,0:13:13.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the area behind the speaker will\Ndefinitely be searched first too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.48,0:13:20.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True. That's why the culprit came here first to\Nclose the stereo's back panel to hide Doyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.61,0:13:23.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.15,0:13:24.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsunashima-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.66,0:13:29.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being the first one to search here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.91,0:13:34.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you could have easily done that while pretending\Nto search behind the stereo, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.33,0:13:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! I saw you searching behind the stereo\Nand you said that you found nothing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.67,0:13:41.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.17,0:13:48.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle probably heard about Doyle's snack\Ntime habits from Kanou-san's parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.47,0:13:51.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As well as about how rarely this speaker was used.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.01,0:13:58.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During a previous visit, you peeled off the\Nacoustic absorber from the speaker,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.65,0:14:03.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and left the back panel open in preparation to hide Doyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.03,0:14:09.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While the speaker would sound strange, it would\Ndivert attention from the suspicious back panel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.49,0:14:14.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could have also recorded the chime\Nby being around for Doyle's snack time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.25,0:14:18.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You then set up the tape and cushion in the stereo,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.00,0:14:24.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,while we were all gathered at the entrance\Nwhen Hasuki-san arrived before noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.67,0:14:31.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You then pretended to search for the missing\NDoyle and went around to the speaker,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.80,0:14:34.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and removed his collar while he was asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.52,0:14:38.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You then retrieved the cushion, and closed the back panel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.56,0:14:45.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You then returned it to the Japanese room,\Nand set the clock back to the correct time,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.11,0:14:50.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And all that's left is to burn the collar in the\Nincinerator and leave the back door open.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.66,0:14:56.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Making it seem like someone had sneaked in, kidnapped\NDoyle, then escaped through the back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.62,0:14:58.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.16,0:15:03.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems like Tsunashima-san wanted to burn the\Nsound absorbent material in the incinerator, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.29,0:15:06.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, glass wool is heat resistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.46,0:15:10.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And most of it remained unburned in the incinerator.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.47,0:15:17.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. That's why Arthur found the cushion in the Japanese\Nroom when he was searching for Doyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.39,0:15:20.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit had returned Doyle's favorite cushion there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.94,0:15:27.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Arthur, why couldn't you sniff\Nout Doyle inside the speaker?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.57,0:15:33.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He knew but couldn't step in here. This is the\Nroom he used to get scolded a lot in after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.58,0:15:41.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But boy, I don't gain any benefits\Nby hiding Doyle in the speakers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.67,0:15:49.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What you were after wasn't Doyle, but\Nwhat was on his collar: this diamond.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.22,0:15:55.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's quite a costly item that Kanou-san's\Ngrandfather bought in France.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.60,0:15:58.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Where'd you find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.72,0:16:01.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was behind the pendulum of the\Nwall clock in the Japanese room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.14,0:16:08.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That clock was accurate at noon. But when I looked\Nagain at three o'clock it was three minutes behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.69,0:16:13.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and at 5 o'clock it was five minutes behind.\NIt was slowing down by a minute every hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.70,0:16:19.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how I knew that something\Nwas stuck behind the pendulum.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.70,0:16:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who hid it there is the one who will be receiving\Nthe clock. Tsunashima-san, that's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.42,0:16:26.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.09,0:16:28.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.96,0:16:29.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsunashima-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.82,0:16:53.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.71,0:17:04.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop that, Arthur!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.08,0:17:09.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't hurt them, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.71,0:17:11.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you really do like dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.13,0:17:14.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you couldn't kill Doyle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.63,0:17:21.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You removed the screws from the back of the speaker\Nso that Doyle could get out when he woke up, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.47,0:17:23.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.06,0:17:27.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Tsunashima-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.65,0:17:28.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.73,0:17:32.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.28,0:17:37.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The number of dogs I have has increased, and\NI needed money badly to expand my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.36,0:17:40.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, you could have sold some of the\Ndogs to decrease the number, couldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.53,0:17:48.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The dogs at my house are mostly\Nabandoned dogs that won't sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.50,0:17:57.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only paths left to them are starvation\Nor poisoning. There are no other options.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.51,0:17:59.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsunashima-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.35,0:18:02.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsunashima-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.77,0:18:04.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.52,0:18:05.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.31,0:18:09.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, please have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.15,0:18:10.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.73,0:18:14.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.32,0:18:17.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's for the dogs at your place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.15,0:18:22.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh Kanou-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.20,0:18:23.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.79,0:18:26.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:32.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think that my deceased grandfather\Nwould have preferred it this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.67,0:18:41.09,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Always
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.67,0:18:41.09,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Song By Mai Kuraki
