Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.95,0:19:49.37,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,{\fs21}Yes, now that the direction of the wind has changed, let's fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.50,0:19:51.25,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,{\fs21}Always give my love
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.75,0:19:54.38,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,{\fs21}Always give my love to you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.08,0:19:55.21,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,{\fs21}Always give my love
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.67,0:20:02.01,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,{\fs21}Always give my, give my love
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.48,0:20:13.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good grief, how shameless.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.44,0:20:17.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the dogs who suffer by being adopted\Nby people who can't afford to keep them!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.52,0:20:21.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, anyway, he did promise to not take in any more dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.82,0:20:24.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But both Arthur and Christie are so amazing, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.61,0:20:28.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Intercepting an escaping criminal, just like police dogs!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.45,0:20:29.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an instinctive action.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.50,0:20:36.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arthur just went after the person who ran from his\Nmaster. And Christie's a shepherd dog by nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.54,0:20:44.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shetland sheep dogs are raised to herd back straying sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.93,0:20:50.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instinctively, they will intercept anyone\Nrunning away from a group.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.02,0:20:53.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really lack imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.06,0:20:56.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's something I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.56,0:21:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why were Hasuki-san's shoes found near the incinerator?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.74,0:21:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's definitely the criminal behind this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.61,0:21:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please hide here for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.49,0:21:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.87,0:21:15.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.33,0:21:22.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arthur! When did you start doing that prank again?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.34,0:21:24.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arthur, are you listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.01,0:21:27.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arthur!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.30,0:21:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must really hate me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.06,0:21:35.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. He just wants you to stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.48,0:21:36.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Arthur?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.56,0:21:44.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said that Arthur had taken your shoes out\Nbefore and waited for you to walk him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.94,0:21:50.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From that, Arthur learned that humans\Ncan't go out without their shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.62,0:21:50.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.45,0:21:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, if he hides your shoes, you won't be\Nable to take his beloved Christie home.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.67,0:22:02.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.09,0:22:07.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, Arthur.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.51,0:22:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because both Christie and I will be going to London\Nwhere you and your master are headed!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.81,0:22:16.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh! Then that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.85,0:22:19.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.06,0:22:22.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I actually came here today to tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.57,0:22:26.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? So you two are actually getting married?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.53,0:22:31.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's great news. Congratulations to you both!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.41,0:22:33.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.24,0:22:36.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We must celebrate before you move away.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.00,0:22:40.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.46,0:22:44.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rest assured, nobody's angry at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.92,0:22:49.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finally!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.68,0:22:53.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were really worried about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.60,0:22:56.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've been really depressed lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.35,0:23:00.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we all thought of ways to lift your spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.56,0:23:02.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasn't included, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.81,0:23:06.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, Conan-kun, you're always\Narguing with Haibara-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.73,0:23:07.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.03,0:23:09.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh really?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.82,0:23:11.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good work, Arthur!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.87,0:23:14.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a great achievement!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.92,0:23:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right. Keep up that expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.00,0:23:29.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With that expression, you'll be seen as just a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.80,0:23:36.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just can't see how you're a 90 year old lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.22,0:23:38.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.52,0:23:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How rude. I'm 84 years old!
